      • create

        public static Well create(String wellName)
        Create a Well.getWell instance for the given well name as a string.
        Parameters:
        wellName - a well name for 96 or 384 well plates.
        Returns:
        a new Well object
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the name is not in 96 or 384 well format.
        NullPointerException - if wellName is null.

      • compute384Well

        public static Well compute384Well(int i,
                                  Well.IndexOrder order)
        Compute the Well for a given index for a 384 well plate. If an index >= 384 is given, then this method will "rollover" the index to make it under 384.
        Parameters:
        i - the index of the well to get
        order - the Well.IndexOrder to use for the given index.
        Returns:
        a Well representing the ith index in the given IndexOrder.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if order is null.
        IllegalArgumentException - if i <0.

      • computeWell

        public static Well computeWell(PlateFormat format,
                               int i,
                               Well.IndexOrder order)
        Compute the Well for the given index for the given plate format. This method will "rollover" the index to make it under the max number of wells per plate.
        Parameters:
        format - the PlateFormat to use.
        i - the index of the well to get
        order - the Well.IndexOrder to use for the given index.
        Returns:
        a Well representing the ith index in the given IndexOrder.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if order or format is null.
        IllegalArgumentException - if i <0.
